result.name: Le Pain Quotidien

reviews.text: Awrsome croissant and breakfast! Lovely rrstaurant and food. I am sure I will come back later for anithe breakfast.

Feels like a living room outside your home. Nice staffs, kids friendly and nice organic food. Opens fairly early in the morning.

The foods are a bit pricy, so make sure you check the menu before going in. If you feel comfortable with the price tag, you'd get comfortable with the whole package.

Ham and cheese croissant and quiche was good. This place is good for English speaking tourists. No Chinese spoken here. Chinese menu said quiche comes with salad AND organic bread. We chased the bread when it didn’t come especially given their branding of being a BAKERY. But waitress snatchrd away the Chinese menu and showed me English one instead, and said she NEVER gives bread with quiche meal. She then wouldn’t give me back the Chinese menu to show her what is written. I asked to speak with the manager. She then decided I could have bread BUT “only this time”. 

Not sure why I was being lectured after being given Chinese menu to order from. Pretty sure Chinese is the official language here. It’s also concerning that it’s ok to rip off your customers because you’ve NEVER done it correctly. No one enjoys getting ripped off and having an argument before my f-ing coffee in the morning. #notsorry

I visit this restaurant quite often; after a stressful day at work I'll have a glass of wine and good food for dinner🍷 (chili con carne in the photo), nice place to have a superb breakfast (in the photo), or just pop in for quick lunch. 🥐🥗 The staff is lovely, and the restaurant itself cozy, warm and welcoming. And clean, which isn't always normal in HK.. Can't recommend the place enough!
Nice coffee, fair price.
